*Assessment*

euform-create-stack doesn't support _parameters_ option (as seen in EUCA-9787).  

Using euca2ools 3.1.0-0.0.202.el6, the following can been seen in the euform-create-stack help documentation:
{quote}
  -p KEY=VALUE, --parameter KEY=VALUE
                        key and value of the parameters to use with the new
                        stack's template, separated by an "=" character
{quote}
This doesn't match the behavior seen in the [cfn-create-stack|https://aws.amazon.com/developertools/AWS-CloudFormation/2555753788650372] documentation:
{quote}
   -p, --parameters "key1=value1;key2=value2..."
       Parameter values used to create the stack.
{quote}

*Signs*

* Error seen when using euca2ools:
{code}
[root@odc-f-13 ~]# euform-create-stack --template-file cfn-example.json --parameter "UbuntuImageId=emi-5FF95D61;Acct1User01KeyPair=account1-user01" DockerStack --region account1-user01@ --debug
